 <p>
  Reply:
  <br/>
  Kim,
  <br/>
  Actually, in ASL you'd sign something like WE-2 MATCH! -- using a large, strong 
movement, and a "very satisfied, affirmative" look on your face.
  <br/>
  It will be a while before you can start "interpreting" ASL. For now just focus 
on going through the lessons and getting a feel for the language.
  <br/>
  - Bill
